<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: DeYoung</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-05-22 16:34:15</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>All those gnome trainers in there hate my Woodelf Ranger, they KOS her.  There are paths that are safe to move around though.  Also, don't be afraid to kill the skellies in there, just don't do it near any of the evil gnome trainers...  Killing them doesn't result in any faction hit and they don't usually gang up either.  The evil gnomes in the mines do cast radiation or something on the skellies though so you likely won't be able to hit one with your weapon.  A little green skellie with 20 hit points nearly took down my level 13 ranger before I figured this out.  Just don't whack them with your weapon.  One cast of my baby DOT spell Flame Lick kills them in just a few seconds.  So I can collect junk weapons to sell and bone chips while I'm waiting for Red V to spawn.  I usually sit in the corner of the room opposite (loc 2149. -630) to kill skells and watch for Red V.  20 times so far and no Bullsmasher yet...  Manik is aimably to me now though, probably soon warmly.  That might help increase the odds, who knows?</font></td></tr></table>
